<p><b>Belgium</b>**<b>, Bolivia, Burkina Faso</b>*<b>, Cameroon, Chile</b>*<b>, Costa Rica</b>*<b>, Cuba, Cyprus</b>*<b>,  
Denmark</b>*<b>, Ecuador</b>*<b>, Estonia</b>*<b>, Finland</b>*<b>, France, Germany, Greece</b>*<b>, Guatemala,  
Ireland</b>*<b>, Italy, Luxembourg</b>*<b>, Mali, Morocco</b>*<b>, Nicaragua, Peru, Portugal</b>*<b>,  
Romania, Slovenia, Spain</b>*<b>, Switzerland, Timor-Leste</b>*<b>, Uruguay:  draft resolution 
</b></p>
<p><b>6/&#8230;  Human rights and equitable access to safe drinking water and sanitation 
</b></p>
<p><i>The Human Rights Council, 
</i></p>
<p><i> Recalling </i>its decision 2/104 of 27 November 2006, 
</p>
<p><i> Welcoming </i>the submission, as requested, by the United Nations High Commissioner for 
Human Rights, of a detailed report on the scope and content of relevant human rights obligations 
related to equitable access to safe drinking water and sanitation under international human rights 
instruments (A/HRC/6/3), 
</p>
<p> <i>Mindful</i> that the report requires thorough consideration by States and other relevant 
stakeholders, 
</p>
<p> 1.  <i>Calls upon </i>all States to give due attention to the report of the High Commissioner 
and to ensure its full dissemination; 
</p>
<p> 2.  <i>Decides</i> to consider the issue at its seventh session. 
----- 
</p>
<p>                                                 
</p>
<p><b>*
</b>  Non-members of the Human Rights Council. </p>

